      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Sam and Maya were friend who loved the sea and old story about distant places in their hometown.",
              "audioStart": 0.1,
              "audioEnd": 4.75
            },
            {
              "text": "One day they found a old map in a box that was covered with dust while cleaning.",
              "audioStart": 5.612,
              "audioEnd": 9.425
            },
            {
              "text": "The map showed a new island that was not on any place they had ever heard before.",
              "audioStart": 10.287,
              "audioEnd": 14.15
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam said the island might hold a great thing that could change their life forever for them.",
              "audioStart": 15.012,
              "audioEnd": 19.262
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya was good and wanted to go there right away because the mystery felt good to them.",
              "audioStart": 20.125,
              "audioEnd": 24.113
            },
            {
              "text": "They plan to start their adventure at dawn the next day with high hope for the adventure.",
              "audioStart": 24.975,
              "audioEnd": 29.087
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Their friend in the town offered help and supplies for the adventure and promised support to them.",
              "audioStart": 29.95,
              "audioEnd": 34.525
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam packed a box, food, water and a small tent that could hold their gear for the trip.",
              "audioStart": 35.388,
              "audioEnd": 40.225
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya took a light, a rope and a book to record the answer they found during the adventure.",
              "audioStart": 41.087,
              "audioEnd": 45.575
            },
            {
              "text": "They left their family and set out by boat at dawn across the calm sea with excitement.",
              "audioStart": 46.438,
              "audioEnd": 50.737
            },
            {
              "text": "The sea was calm and the air was soft as they sailed toward the island in the early morning.",
              "audioStart": 51.6,
              "audioEnd": 55.737
            },
            {
              "text": "If the weather had been bad they would have turned back, but the sky was clear and bright.",
              "audioStart": 56.6,
              "audioEnd": 60.85
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "After a few hours a dark storm came over the water and the air howled with great force.",
              "audioStart": 61.712,
              "audioEnd": 66.162
            },
            {
              "text": "The boat moved hard and the rope almost broke because the water was strong during the storm.",
              "audioStart": 67.025,
              "audioEnd": 71.375
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam kept calm and used a light to see the path that led forward despite the noise.",
              "audioStart": 72.237,
              "audioEnd": 76.625
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya helped by holding the rope and reading the map that showed the next direction carefully.",
              "audioStart": 77.487,
              "audioEnd": 81.825
            },
            {
              "text": "The storm passed and the sea became calm again, allowing them to continue their adventure safely as the sun rose.",
              "audioStart": 82.688,
              "audioEnd": 88.725
            },
            {
              "text": "They felt proud because they had worked together and lived through the danger without fear of the night.",
              "audioStart": 89.588,
              "audioEnd": 94.188
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "At dawn they saw the land of the new island covered with green trees and bright sky above the water.",
              "audioStart": 95.05,
              "audioEnd": 100
            },
            {
              "text": "The island was covered with trees and a small cave near the beach that smelled of sea near the dawn.",
              "audioStart": 100.862,
              "audioEnd": 105.612
            },
            {
              "text": "Inside the cave they found a stone with a question marked on it for anyone to answer that glowed faintly.",
              "audioStart": 106.475,
              "audioEnd": 111.487
            },
            {
              "text": "The question read what has many eyes can not see and it made them think hard in the dim light.",
              "audioStart": 112.35,
              "audioEnd": 117.075
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam thought the answer was a storm because a storm has many eyes of clouds in the sky.",
              "audioStart": 117.938,
              "audioEnd": 122.275
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya said the answer was a potato because a potato has many eyes and can not move on the farm.",
              "audioStart": 123.138,
              "audioEnd": 128.162
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "A small bird flew down and landed on Maya hand and looked at them curiously in the bright light.",
              "audioStart": 129.025,
              "audioEnd": 133.887
            },
            {
              "text": "The bird chirped and seemed to guide them toward a new path that led deeper into the island through the forest.",
              "audioStart": 134.75,
              "audioEnd": 139.812
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam and Maya followed the bird and found a stone bridge over a deep river that glimmered under the moon.",
              "audioStart": 140.675,
              "audioEnd": 145.662
            },
            {
              "text": "The bridge was old but safe and they crossed it together without any trouble during the night.",
              "audioStart": 146.525,
              "audioEnd": 150.787
            },
            {
              "text": "When they reached the other side they saw a box with a lock that shone in the light on the sand.",
              "audioStart": 151.65,
              "audioEnd": 156.225
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya used the rope to pull the lock open and the box was full of bright stones that sparkled.",
              "audioStart": 157.088,
              "audioEnd": 161.713
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Inside the box a second question was written on a piece of paper that glowed softly in the dark.",
              "audioStart": 162.575,
              "audioEnd": 167.537
            },
            {
              "text": "The question asked what can travel around the world while staying in one place and it puzzled them for many travelers.",
              "audioStart": 168.4,
              "audioEnd": 174.325
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam guessed a ship but Maya said the answer was a stamp because a stamp travels on a letter every day.",
              "audioStart": 175.188,
              "audioEnd": 180.412
            },
            {
              "text": "They realized the answer was a stamp because a stamp can travel on a letter without moving in the post.",
              "audioStart": 181.275,
              "audioEnd": 186.525
            },
            {
              "text": "The box also held a map that showed a route to a new cave with a treasure inside deep underground.",
              "audioStart": 187.387,
              "audioEnd": 192.238
            },
            {
              "text": "They decided to follow the route together because they knew work together was their greatest strength in the face of challenge.",
              "audioStart": 193.1,
              "audioEnd": 198.8
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "At the end of the route they entered a bright cave filled with gold and many gems that glittered deep inside.",
              "audioStart": 199.662,
              "audioEnd": 204.688
            },
            {
              "text": "The treasure was a set of ancient books that told the history of the island and its people to future people.",
              "audioStart": 205.55,
              "audioEnd": 210.463
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam read a page that said the real treasure was knowledge and friend for those who seek in the quiet night.",
              "audioStart": 211.325,
              "audioEnd": 216.287
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya felt good and agreed that they had learned to work together and help each other forever with a smile.",
              "audioStart": 217.15,
              "audioEnd": 221.925
            },
            {
              "text": "The island was a place where anyone could find a thing if they were good and kind in their heart.",
              "audioStart": 222.787,
              "audioEnd": 227.338
            },
            {
              "text": "They left the island with the books the stones and a new sense of purpose for adventure and hope.",
              "audioStart": 228.2,
              "audioEnd": 233.848
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "The boat returned to the town and the people welcomed them as a great friend of the sea after the long adventure.",
              "audioStart": 234.71,
              "audioEnd": 239.96
            },
            {
              "text": "Sam told the story to the child and they listened with great interest and joy in the evening.",
              "audioStart": 240.823,
              "audioEnd": 245.161
            },
            {
              "text": "Maya thanked the bird for its help and promised to visit the island again soon with gratitude.",
              "audioStart": 246.023,
              "audioEnd": 250.523
            },
            {
              "text": "They both agreed that work together and help were the key to any adventure they might face in every moment.",
              "audioStart": 251.386,
              "audioEnd": 256.523
            },
            {
              "text": "The map was now kept safe in the town library for future adventure and for new person who seeks.",
              "audioStart": 257.385,
              "audioEnd": 262.461
            },
            {
              "text": "Their story became a story that showed the value of help, good and friend for all in the world.",
              "audioStart": 263.323,
              "audioEnd": 267.923
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
